<typeStatus box="[302,400,1474,1498]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected from near Tong–sha Islands, the South 
<collectingCountry box="[1005,1072,1474,1498]" name="China" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">China</collectingCountry>
Sea. Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Richards" box="[1246,1427,1474,1498]" firstAuthor="Richards" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="2359 - 2382" refId="ref51424" refString="Richards, W. J. (1999) Family Triglidae. In Carpenter, K. E. &amp; V. H. Niem. (eds) Species identification guide for fishery purposes. The living marine resources of the western central Pacific. v. 4, Bony fishes part 2 (Mugilidae to Carangidae). FAO, Rome, pp. 2359 - 2382." type="book chapter" year="1999">Richards (1999)</bibRefCitation>
recognized this species as valid, Dr. T. Kawai (pers. comm., 
<date box="[876,1007,1513,1537]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" value="2008-06-04">4 Jun. 2008</date>
) suggested that we should follow 
<bibRefCitation author="Miller" box="[199,350,1552,1576]" firstAuthor="Miller" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="61 - 72" refId="ref49252" refString="Miller, G. C. (1974) Fische des Indian Ozeans. Ergebnisse der ichthyologischen Untersuchungen wa ¨ hrend der Expedition des Forschungsschiffes '' Meteor' ' in den Indischen Ozean, Oktober 1964 bis Mai 1965. A. Systematischer Teil, XIV, Scorpaeniformes (2) Family Peristediidae. Meteor Forschergeb Reihe D Biol, 18, 61 - 72." type="journal article" year="1974">Miller (1974)</bibRefCitation>
and treat it as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lloyd" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[748,955,1552,1576]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Peristediidae" genus="Satyrichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="adeni">
